  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary condition inputs; a screening sensitivity study was conducted informally during model development and results are summarized in the UQ narrative, confirming that inlet flow rate and rotational speed are the dominant drivers. Formal structured sensitivity analysis records are incorporated within the UQ documentation package.",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
