      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable; fluid temperature, hematocrit, and flow rates recorded with calibrated instrumentation.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data used. Test conditions documented in Hariharan et al. (2011): bovine blood at 37 °C, hematocrit 33±3%, flow rates measured with calibrated Coriolis flowmeter (±0.5%). All boundary conditions in the CFD model set to match reported experimental values."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or U_val) reported; model error within experimental uncertainty band for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions compared using E% metric per ASME V&V 20. At all 5 operating points, |E%| ≤ 12.8%. Combined validation uncertainty U_val computed from experimental and numerical contributions; model error falls within U_val at 4 of 5 points. The single outlier at 4 LPM/2500 RPM is within 1.4×U_val, deemed acceptable given conservative hemolysis model assumptions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH index); hemolysis scalar transport equation outputs NIH which converts to RH.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which is algebraically converted to the relative hemolysis index (RH) used in the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1. The QoI chain is direct and without surrogate substitution. Shear exposure history integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks provides mechanistic basis for NIH."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
