      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated; residuals reduced by at least 4 orders of magnitude and QoI monitor stable.",
      "rationale": "All simulations run to convergence with mass, momentum, and turbulence residuals below 1×10⁻⁵. NIH monitor value varies by less than 0.3% over the final 500 iterations. Steady-state MRF approach validated against transient sliding mesh for one operating point with < 2% difference in NIH."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 when model influence is Medium and independent review of setup is documented.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 with Medium model influence, formal use-error assessment is not required per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Simulation setup reviewed by a second analyst who confirmed boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and post-processing scripts. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection justified by literature precedent for similar pump geometries.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published literature demonstrating superior performance for rotating blood-contacting devices (Fraser et al., 2011; Hariharan et al., 2011). Formal model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2. Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model is the community standard for CFD hemolysis prediction."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties documented with sources; input uncertainty ranges defined for UQ propagation.",
      "rationale": "Thirteen model inputs catalogued with nominal values and uncertainty ranges derived from device manufacturing tolerances and physiological literature: inlet flow rate (±5%), rotational speed (±50 RPM), blood viscosity (±8%), hematocrit (±3%), and geometric tolerances (±0.05 mm on critical clearances). Input uncertainty ranges propagated through the model via Monte Carlo sampling (n=200 Latin hypercube draws). A screening sensitivity study conducted during model development indicated that inlet flow rate and rotational speed account for approximately 78% of NIH output variance, with geometric clearance contributing an additional 14%; these findings are documented in the UQ analysis report and informed the prioritization of boundary condition fidelity in the validation plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
