    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with Medium model influence. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo propagation (n=200 LHS draws) demonstrates that NIH predictions remain below the RH < 1 threshold across the 95th percentile of the sampled input space. The UQ analysis report documents a screening sensitivity study identifying inlet flow rate and rotational speed as dominant variance contributors, providing confidence that the most influential inputs have been characterized. The model is accepted as fit for the purpose of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device regulatory submission.",
